<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuan Zhao et Zhu L. Yang" authorityYear="2014" box="[532,660,231,252]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletaceae" genus="Rubroboletus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[532,660,231,252]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Rubroboletus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is characterized by its rose-red to dark red pileal surface covered with brownish scales, ovoid-ellipsoid spores with an inconspicuous suprahilar depression and a bluish color change when bruised (
<bibRefCitation author="Chiu, W. F." box="[1341,1447,267,289]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" pagination="199 - 231" refId="ref7507" refString="Chiu, W. F. (1948) The boletes of Yunnan. Mycologia 40: 199 - 231. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 3755085" type="journal article" year="1948">Chiu 1948</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chiu, W. F." box="[189,241,303,325]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" refId="ref7540" refString="Chiu, W. F. (1957) Altas of Yunnan boletes. Science Press, Beijing, 156 pp. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="1957">1957</bibRefCitation>
